{"node_id": "517531b3cba059fe910d3e2b9e959448", "title": "The fundamental theorem of calculus and definite integrals", "description": "Use the fundamental theorem of calculus to find definite integrals.", "topic_path": ["Khan Academy (English - US curriculum)", "Math", "AP®︎ Calculus AB", "Integration and accumulation of change", "The fundamental theorem of calculus and definite integrals", "The fundamental theorem of calculus and definite integrals"], "assessment_items": [{"item_id": "893f65dfb14e59979cb636d08c52f04d", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&F(x)=4x^2-5x\n\\\\\\\\\n&f(x)=F'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_1^4 f(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$f$ is the derivative of $F$, which means $F$ is an antiderivative of $f$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $f$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $f$ and its antiderivative $F$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b f(x)\\,dx=F(b)-F(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_1^4 f(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=F(\\blueD{4})-F(\\blueD{1})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=[4(\\blueD{4})^2-5(\\blueD{4})]-[4(\\blueD{1})^2-5(\\blueD{1})]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=44-(-1)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=45\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_1^4 f(x)\\,dx=45$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 45}]}}}, {"item_id": "e3d5e1f14ade5eb19c37bef89487e8ee", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&G(x)=\\sqrt{3x}\n\\\\\\\\\n&g(x)=G'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{3}^{12} g(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$g$ is the derivative of $G$, which means $G$ is an antiderivative of $g$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $g$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $g$ and its antiderivative $G$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b g(x)\\,dx=G(b)-G(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{3}^{12} g(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=G(\\blueD{12})-G(\\blueD{3})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\sqrt{3\\blueD{(12)}}-\\sqrt{3\\blueD{(3)}}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=6-3\n\\\\\\\\\n&=3\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{3}^{12} g(x)\\,dx=3$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 3}]}}}, {"item_id": "db919a0c92915490aaae010acf6c4095", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&H(x)=10^{x}\n\\\\\\\\\n&h(x)=H'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-3}^{2} h(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$h$ is the derivative of $H$, which means $H$ is an antiderivative of $h$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $h$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $h$ and its antiderivative $H$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b h(x)\\,dx=H(b)-H(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{-3}^{2} h(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=H(\\blueD{2})-H(\\blueD{-3})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\left[10^{\\blueD{2}}\\right]-\\left[10^{\\blueD{-3}}\\right]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=100-0.001\n\\\\\\\\\n&=99.999\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-3}^{2} h(x)\\,dx=99.999$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 99.999}]}}}, {"item_id": "50205d513ff6507c8b2dc201651c591e", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&F(x)=|4x-20|\n\\\\\\\\\n&f(x)=F'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-5}^{5} f(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$f$ is the derivative of $F$, which means $F$ is an antiderivative of $f$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $f$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $f$ and its antiderivative $F$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b f(x)\\,dx=F(b)-F(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{-5}^{5} f(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=F(\\blueD{5})-F(\\blueD{-5})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=|4\\blueD{(5)}-20|-|4\\blueD{(-5)}-20|\n\\\\\\\\\n&=0-40\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-40\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-5}^{5} f(x)\\,dx=-40$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": -40}]}}}, {"item_id": "8b70c91aff7c552bb006b34ccbd890d6", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&G(x)=2x^3-4\n\\\\\\\\\n&g(x)=G'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{1}^{2} g(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$g$ is the derivative of $G$, which means $G$ is an antiderivative of $g$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $g$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $g$ and its antiderivative $G$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b g(x)\\,dx=G(b)-G(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{1}^{2} g(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=G(\\blueD{2})-G(\\blueD{1})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=[2\\blueD{(2)}^3-4]-[2\\blueD{(1)}^3-4]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=12-(-2)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=14\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{1}^{2} g(x)\\,dx=14$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 14}]}}}, {"item_id": "c61717b5579053f6988b5cd858eb4955", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&H(x)=-x-5\n\\\\\\\\\n&h(x)=H'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-3}^{6} h(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$h$ is the derivative of $H$, which means $H$ is an antiderivative of $h$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $h$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $h$ and its antiderivative $H$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b h(x)\\,dx=H(b)-H(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{-3}^{6} h(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=H(\\blueD{6})-H(\\blueD{-3})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=[-\\blueD{6}-5]-[-\\blueD{(-3)}-5]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-11-(-2)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-9\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-3}^{6} h(x)\\,dx=-9$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": -9}]}}}, {"item_id": "7c18aa0f429d5e2bb45a8718c90f1f30", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&F(x)=\\sqrt{x+7}\n\\\\\\\\\n&f(x)=F'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{2}^{9} f(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$f$ is the derivative of $F$, which means $F$ is an antiderivative of $f$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $f$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $f$ and its antiderivative $F$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b f(x)\\,dx=F(b)-F(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{2}^{9} f(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=F(\\blueD{9})-F(\\blueD{2})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\sqrt{\\blueD{9}+7}-\\sqrt{\\blueD{2}+7}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=4-3\n\\\\\\\\\n&=1\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{2}^{9} f(x)\\,dx=1$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 1}]}}}, {"item_id": "00520ca7709a5c65b6bf6da1d42e6bd0", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&G(x)=\\cos(3x)\n\\\\\\\\\n&g(x)=G'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{0}^{\\pi} g(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$g$ is the derivative of $G$, which means $G$ is an antiderivative of $g$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $g$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $g$ and its antiderivative $G$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b g(x)\\,dx=G(b)-G(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{0}^{\\pi} g(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=G(\\blueD{\\pi})-G(\\blueD{0})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\cos(3\\blueD{(\\pi)})-\\cos(3\\blueD{(0)})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-1-1\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-2\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{0}^{\\pi} g(x)\\,dx=-2$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": -2}]}}}, {"item_id": "d33e935ffdf3534eb2be22af5e35c99c", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&H(x)=\\left|\\dfrac{x}{2}\\right|\n\\\\\\\\\n&h(x)=H'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-6}^{-2} h(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$h$ is the derivative of $H$, which means $H$ is an antiderivative of $h$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $h$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $h$ and its antiderivative $H$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b h(x)\\,dx=H(b)-H(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{-6}^{-2} h(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=H(\\blueD{-2})-H(\\blueD{-6})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\left|\\dfrac{\\blueD{-2}}{2}\\right|-\\left|\\dfrac{\\blueD{-6}}{2}\\right|\n\\\\\\\\\n&=1-3\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-2\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-6}^{-2} h(x)\\,dx=-2$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": -2}]}}}, {"item_id": "ccf6ee844faa5149949000c4447494f6", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&F(x)=5^{x}\n\\\\\\\\\n&f(x)=F'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{0}^{3} f(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$f$ is the derivative of $F$, which means $F$ is an antiderivative of $f$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $f$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $f$ and its antiderivative $F$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b f(x)\\,dx=F(b)-F(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{0}^{3} f(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=F(\\blueD{3})-F(\\blueD{0})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=5^{\\blueD{3}}-5^{\\blueD{0}}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=125-1\n\\\\\\\\\n&=124\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{0}^{3} f(x)\\,dx=124$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 124}]}}}, {"item_id": "e1dd591ec39f529b8e3153cc88ffab57", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&G(x)=(x+3)^2\n\\\\\\\\\n&g(x)=G'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-1}^{7} g(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$g$ is the derivative of $G$, which means $G$ is an antiderivative of $g$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $g$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $g$ and its antiderivative $G$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b g(x)\\,dx=G(b)-G(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{-1}^{7} g(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=G(\\blueD{7})-G(\\blueD{-1})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=(\\blueD{7}+3)^2-(\\blueD{-1}+3)^2\n\\\\\\\\\n&=100-4\n\\\\\\\\\n&=96\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-1}^{7} g(x)\\,dx=96$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 96}]}}}, {"item_id": "a52c5adea94a548f93f8eec976340044", "question_content": "$\\begin{align}\n&H(x)=3x^2-6\n\\\\\\\\\n&h(x)=H'(x)\n\\end{align}$\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-1}^{0} h(x)\\,dx=$ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["$h$ is the derivative of $H$, which means $H$ is an antiderivative of $h$.\n\nSince we know the antiderivative of $h$, we can use the fundamental theorem of calculus: For every function $h$ and its antiderivative $H$,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_a^b h(x)\\,dx=H(b)-H(a)$.", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\displaystyle\\int_{-1}^{0} h(x)\\,dx\n\\\\\\\\\n&=H(\\blueD{0})-H(\\blueD{-1})\n\\\\\\\\\n&=[3\\blueD{(0)}^2-6]-[3\\blueD{(-1)}^2-6]\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-6-(-3)\n\\\\\\\\\n&=-3\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int_{-1}^{0} h(x)\\,dx=-3$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": -3}]}}}], "mastery_model": {"type": "m_of_n", "m": 3, "n": 4}, "randomize": true}